# Cloning a Github Repository

By cloning a repository the repository will be copied to the local disk.

Cloning is **not forking**.

## Use cases for a cloned repository

* Look at the project
* Install the project
* Follow the changes

## What you cannot do with a cloned repo

* **You cannot create pull requests !!** 

## Git Commands

### Cloning

    git clone https://github/user/project

The clone command creates a new subdirectory and copies the project into this subdirectory


### Getting Information

    git remote -v

### Getting Updates from the remote repository

    git fetch origin